@Jin's response made me snortle, but it's likely correct. you might have a stray 0 in place of an O--that's a common error. You may have an incorrect answer you're sure of but shouldn't be. you may have accidentally hit the rebus button and ended up with a hidden space after a character that looks correct in the grid. 

If you don't care about streaks then hit reveal puzzle and find the error.  If you do care and don't consider it cheating to look at the answer key or xwordinfo, do that. And by all means do come back with an update.

